"{\"uid\": \"christies.com-en-stories-bob-beamon-olympic-gold-medal-f5f44e653f544ed29f000d4f35698ffa\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"At the politically charged '68 Games in Mexico City, Beamon broke boundaries with a world record jump and a historic stand for equality      With 19 impressive strides down the runway, he hit the board perfectly, ascended into the air like a bird, and firmly planted his feet in the sand six seconds later.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 40, \"end\": 51, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999854795286537, \"rank\": 1.4520682054414474e-05, \"text\": \"Mexico City\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bob Beamon's sets a new world record in long jump at the 1968 Mexico City Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Photograph: Ed Lacey/Popperfoto via Getty Images  Beamon had leaped where no one had landed before: an incredible 8.90 meters, or 29 feet, 2 \\u00bd inches, smashing the world and Olympic records, the latter of which still stands.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beamon had landed so far beyond the distance measurable by the optical rail, that officials had to take out a measuring tape to manually measure the jump.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I was truly relaxed and felt like I could float over water,' Beamon recalls of the moment.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beamon's Olympic gold medal will be offered inThe Exceptional Saleon 1 February 2024 at Christie's in New York.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999878618838, \"rank\": 1.0653572983149391e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medal represents the pinnacle of Beamon's athletic career as well as an irreplaceable piece of Olympic history.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Conceptualized by Italian artist Giuseppe Cassiolo, the medal design shows a robed goddess of victory, with a palm in her left hand and a winner's crown aloft in her right.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9855675004889949, \"rank\": 0.01067410414050306, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals from the '68 Games feature the inscriptionXIX OLIMIADA MEXICO 1968in a font that combines influences from 1960s Op Art and the traditional patterns of the Indigenous Huichol peoples of Mexico.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1392, \"end\": 1398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Op_art\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Op Art\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Op_art\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Op_art\"}, {\"begin\": 1446, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huichol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.518633898895958e-16, \"text\": \"Huichol\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huichol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huichol\"}, {\"begin\": 1465, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9999986642855955, \"rank\": 1.0744379142679493e-06, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the reverse is an Olympic champion carried in triumph by the crowd.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An Olympic gold medal presented to Bob Beamon for the men's long jump, Mexico, 1968.2 3\\u20448 in (6cm) diameter, 4 oz.\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.5929029928827556, \"rank\": 0.35179399388329236, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\"}, {\"begin\": 1616, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9999986642855955, \"rank\": 1.0744379142679493e-06, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2 dwt.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(128 gr.).\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sold for $441,000 inThe Exceptional Saleon 1 February 2024 at Christie's in New York        The boycott was met with disapproval from the university, costing Beamon his place on the team, as well as his scholarship.\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'And so we lost our scholarship, but we all stayed focused,' said Beamon.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Undeterred, he  continued to train, eventually qualifying for the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 2048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was against this backdrop of civil unrest and personal uncertainty that Beamon competed in the 1968 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He persevered and won by a landslide.\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2205, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beamon's monster jump proved so iconic it inspired a new word -Beamonesque- to denote an astonishing athletic feat.\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'After digesting all of this, it was time to get up on the award stand and get this wonderful, incredible medal.'\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beamon says.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I was between time and space because I did not quite understand what I had done.'\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Beamon clearly understood the magnitude of the moment, that millions of eyes would be focused on him as he mounted the podium.\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just two days prior, African American track and field athletes Tommie Smith and John Carlos stood on the Olympic podium and raised black-gloved fists in the Black Power Salute, in the wake of King's assassination.\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9999926091464025, \"rank\": 7.323957472909524e-06, \"text\": \"African American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommie Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Carlos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\"}, {\"begin\": 2857, \"end\": 2861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"score\": 0.6499581383746007, \"rank\": 0.49341149653657873, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bob Beamon victorious on Olympic medal podium after winning gold.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2880, \"end\": 2883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.5929029928827556, \"rank\": 0.35179399388329236, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Photograph: Rich Clarkson/Sports Illustrated via Getty Image      From a sport perspective, Beamon's medal represents the gold standard of otherworldly performances Culturally, it is a tangible piece of Americana that commemorates Beamon's unwavering integrity against all odds.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2958, \"end\": 2971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rich_Clarkson\", \"score\": 0.9999736325014252, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rich Clarkson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rich_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rich_Clarkson\"}, {\"begin\": 2972, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.037151447804975e-12, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up for Going Once, a weekly newsletter delivering our top stories and art market insights to your inbox\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3334, \"entities\": []}]}"